    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-09T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-09T14:00:00-05:00" n="806"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d806">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48: Refugees/1608: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-09T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 9, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 9—4:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>648. Saw MacDonald this evening. The Government tomorrow will accept the experts’
                    report on British Guiana<note n="58" xml:id="d806fn58">British Cmd. 6014: <hi
                            rend="italic">Report of the British Guiana Refugee Commission to the
                            Advisory Committee on Political Refugees appointed by the President of
                            the United States of America</hi>, May 1939; and British Cmd. 6029: <hi
                            rend="italic">Appendices to the Report …</hi>
                    </note> for settlement of the Jews in a preliminary statement and will indicate
                    their willingness to proceed to help on the colonization.</p>
                <p>MacDonald is sending to Lindsay<note n="59" xml:id="d806fn59">Sir Ronald Lindsay,
                        British Ambassador in the United States.</note> tomorrow the White Paper on
                    Palestine which he proposes to make public next Monday<note n="60"
                        xml:id="d806fn60">May 15.</note> in Parliament. Lindsay has instructions to
                    show it to you immediately on arrival. I judge from what he told me in a general
                    way that the Jews will not be pleased with it, but the Government feels that it
                    cannot delay the matter any longer and that it has made the only fair
                    decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
